{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:51:25.760Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the revolutionary optimization algorithm that powers nearly all modern deep learning and neural network training—it updates model parameters after processing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "just one data point at a time"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (or a small batch), introducing randomness that makes it faster, more scalable, and able to escape local minima compared to standard gradient descent."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Stochastic Gradient Descent — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Core concept:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a variant of the gradient descent algorithm that updates parameters using a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "single randomly chosen data point"}, {"type": "text", "text": " at each iteration, rather than the entire dataset."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key difference from standard GD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Algorithm"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient computation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch GD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uses ALL N samples: ∇J(θ) = (1/N) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ ∇Jᵢ(θ)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uses ONE sample: ∇J(θ) ≈ ∇Jᵢ(θ) for randomly chosen i"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mini-batch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uses B samples: ∇J(θ) = (1/B) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴬ ∇Jᵢ(θ)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical formula:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "θ_new = θ_old - η × ∇Jᵢ(θ)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = model parameters (weights, biases)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "η"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = learning rate\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "∇Jᵢ(θ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = gradient of loss for single sample i\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "i"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = randomly chosen index from dataset"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why \"stochastic\"?"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The term \"stochastic\" means "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "random or probabilistic"}, {"type": "text", "text": "—SGD introduces randomness by selecting one data point at random for each update, making the optimization path noisy and unpredictable."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How SGD works — Step-by-step algorithm"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Initialize model parameters (weights & bias) randomly\n   θ ← random values [web:278]\n\n2. Shuffle the dataset randomly\n   This ensures different order each epoch [web:278]\n\n3. Iterate through each data point:\n   For each sample (xᵢ, yᵢ):\n   a. Compute prediction: y_pred = model(xᵢ, θ) [web:278][web:283]\n   b. Calculate loss: Lᵢ = loss(y_pred, yᵢ) [web:278]\n   c. Compute gradient: ∇Jᵢ(θ) = gradient of loss w.r.t. θ [web:278][web:283]\n   d. Update parameters: θ = θ - η × ∇Jᵢ(θ) [web:278][web:281]\n\n4. Repeat for multiple epochs until convergence\n   Typically 10-1000 epochs depending on dataset [web:278]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD vs Batch Gradient Descent — Key differences"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speed and Efficiency"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch GD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Slow for large datasets (must compute N gradients per update)\n- Computationally expensive when N is large (millions)\n- Requires storing entire dataset in memory"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Fast updates (just 1 gradient per step)\n- Can perform updates before seeing all data\n- Ideal for large datasets and online learning\n- Lower memory requirement (only 1 sample at time)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence Behavior"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch GD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth, direct path to minimum\nLoss converges smoothly as gradient is averaged over all samples [web:279]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noisy, zigzag path: Hops around, oscillates toward minimum\nHops around on its path to the minimum on the loss surface [web:281]\n\nSince GD considers entire dataset → smoother convergence\nSGD uses single point → oscillating convergence [web:279]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Escape Local Minima"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch GD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Can get stuck in local minima (deterministic, smooth path)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noise helps escape local minima"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (especially in non-convex problems like neural networks)\n- Randomness enables exploration of optimization landscape"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scalability"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dataset Size"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Batch GD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small (N < 1000)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast but noisy"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Medium (N = 10,000)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large (N > 100,000)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very slow"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best choice"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Streaming/Online"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impossible"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Perfect fit"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why SGD is better for large datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- GD considers entire dataset → computationally expensive\n- SGD uses only 1 data point → faster and scalable"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why SGD is essential for Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why SGD is critical"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep Learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Foundation for training neural networks with millions/billions of parameters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large Datasets"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Training GPT-4 on billions of tokens requires SGD (batch GD impossible)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Online Learning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models can learn from streaming data in real-time"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-convex Optimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Helps escape local minima in complex neural network loss surfaces"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory Efficiency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lower memory requirements than batch GD"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training modern AI models like GPT, DALL-E, or Stable Diffusion uses mini-batch SGD (batch size 32-512) because computing gradients over billions of training samples is computationally infeasible."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mini-batch SGD — The practical compromise"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD with a single point is too noisy; mini-batch SGD is the standard approach."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mini-batch SGD:\n- Use B samples per update (e.g., B = 32, 64, 128)\n- Average gradients over batch: ∇J(θ) = (1/B) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴬ ∇Jᵢ(θ)\n\nBenefits:\n- Faster updates than batch GD\n- More stable than pure SGD\n- Computational efficiency (batch operations on GPU) [web:266][web:281]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tradebacks"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size = 1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Pure SGD (fastest, most noisy)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size = small (32-64)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Mini-batch SGD (balanced)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Batch size = N"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Batch GD (stable, slow)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Challenges of SGD"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noisy Updates"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD path: Hops around significantly\nBatch GD path: Smooth convergence [web:279]\n\nNoise can cause oscillation near minimum instead of smooth convergence\nSolution: Use mini-batch or learning rate schedules [web:278]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Oscillating Convergence"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD may oscillate near minimum instead of settling\nSolution: Decrease learning rate over time [web:279][web:281]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence to Suboptimal Points"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noise can sometimes lead to local minima instead of global\nSolution: Use momentum, adaptive methods (Adam) [web:279]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning Rate Schedules for SGD"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Since SGD is noisy, using a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " often leads to poor convergence. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": " gradually decrease η over time to refine the solution."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant Learning Rate"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η = 0.01 (fixed throughout training)\n\nPros: Simple\nCons: May overshoot or converge slowly [web:266]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Default schedule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Default uses constant learning rate for each training epoch"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step Decay (Time-based)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(epoch) = η₀ / (1 + decay × epoch)\n\nReduce LR by factor (e.g., 10×) at fixed epochs [web:266]\n\nExample:\nEpoch 0-30: η = 0.1\nEpoch 31-60: η = 0.01\nEpoch 61-90: η = 0.001 [web:266]\n\nPros: Large steps early, fine-tuning later\nCons: Requires knowing when to decay [web:266]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The SGD implementation has a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": " argument for time-based learning rate decay."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential Decay"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(epoch) = η₀ × exp(-decay × epoch)\n\nSmooth exponential decrease [web:280]\n\nPros: Automatic decay\nCons: Requires tuning decay parameter"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine Annealing"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(t) = η_min + (η_max - η_min) × (1 + cos(π × t/T)) / 2\n\nLR follows cosine curve from max to min over T epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Smooth decay, often achieves better accuracy\nCons: Requires tuning T"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning Rate Warmup"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start with small η, increase to max, then decrease:\n\nη(t) = small → η_max → η_min\n\nPopularized by fast.ai; often achieves same accuracy in fewer epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Prevents early divergence, improves convergence\nCons: Adds complexity"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive Decay (Validation-based)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluate validation set after each epoch\nReduce LR when validation loss change < threshold\n\nTends to give good convergence to local optima [web:263]\n\nPros: Automatic, adaptive to training progress\nCons: Requires validation set"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why learning rate schedules work:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start high for fast progress across the loss surface\nGradually decrease to refine solution near minimum [web:266]\n\nLarge η early: Fast exploration, escape local minima\nSmall η late: Precise convergence to minimum"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common SGD Variants"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD with Momentum"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vₜ = γ × vₜ₋₁ + η × ∇Jᵢ(θ)\nθ = θ - vₜ\n\nWhere:\n- v = velocity (accumulated gradient)\n- γ = momentum coefficient (e.g., 0.9)\n\nBenefit: Smooths noisy SGD updates, accelerates in consistent direction [web:268][web:274]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NAdam (Nesterov Adaptive Momentum)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Combines momentum with adaptive learning rates (like Adam)\nBenefit: Faster convergence, better for deep networks [web:274]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adam (Adaptive Moment Estimation)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adaptive learning rates per parameter based on:\n- First moment (mean of gradients)\n- Second moment (variance of gradients)\n\nBenefit: Faster convergence, less tuning needed [web:268][web:274]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python Implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pure SGD (single sample):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Initialize parameters\ntheta = np.random.randn(10)  # 10 weights\neta = 0.01  # learning rate\n\n# Training loop\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    for i in range(len(X)):  # Iterate through all samples\n        # Pick random sample\n        x_i = X[i]\n        y_i = y[i]\n        \n        # Compute prediction\n        y_pred = np.dot(x_i, theta)\n        \n        # Compute loss (MSE for single sample)\n        loss = (y_pred - y_i) ** 2\n        \n        # Compute gradient\n        gradient = 2 * (y_pred - y_i) * x_i\n        \n        # Update parameters\n        theta = theta - eta * gradient"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mini-batch SGD (practical):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef mini_batch_sgd(X, y, eta=0.01, batch_size=32, epochs=100):\n    n_samples = len(X)\n    theta = np.random.randn(X.shape [medium](https://medium.com/@lomashbhuva/stochastic-gradient-descent-sgd-a-comprehensive-guide-to-faster-machine-learning-b3afaf496a52))\n    \n    for epoch in range(epochs):\n        # Shuffle data\n        indices = np.random.permutation(n_samples)\n        X_shuffled = X[indices]\n        y_shuffled = y[indices]\n        \n        # Iterate through mini-batches\n        for i in range(0, n_samples, batch_size):\n            # Get batch\n            X_batch = X_shuffled[i:i+batch_size]\n            y_batch = y_shuffled[i:i+batch_size]\n            \n            # Compute prediction\n            y_pred = np.dot(X_batch, theta)\n            \n            # Compute loss\n            loss = np.mean((y_pred - y_batch) ** 2)\n            \n            # Compute gradient (average over batch)\n            gradient = 2 * np.mean((y_pred - y_batch) * X_batch, axis=0)\n            \n            # Update parameters\n            theta = theta - eta * gradient\n        \n        print(f\"Epoch {epoch}: Loss = {loss:.4f}\")\n    \n    return theta"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SGD with learning rate schedule:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nfrom sklearn.datasets import make_regression\n\n# Generate data\nX, y = make_regression(n_samples=1000, n_features=10)\n\n# SGD with time-based decay\neta_0 = 0.1\ndecay = 0.01\ntheta = np.random.randn(X.shape [medium](https://medium.com/@lomashbhuva/stochastic-gradient-descent-sgd-a-comprehensive-guide-to-faster-machine-learning-b3afaf496a52))\n\nfor epoch in range(100):\n    eta = eta_0 / (1 + decay * epoch)  # Step decay\n    \n    for i in range(len(X)):\n        # Pick random sample\n        idx = np.random.randint(len(X))\n        x_i = X[idx]\n        y_i = y[idx]\n        \n        # Update\n        y_pred = np.dot(x_i, theta)\n        gradient = 2 * (y_pred - y_i) * x_i\n        theta = theta - eta * gradient\n    \n    print(f\"Epoch {epoch}: LR = {eta:.4f}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD = stochastic (random) updates"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uses 1 sample per update instead of entire dataset"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": θ = θ - η × ∇Jᵢ(θ) for randomly chosen sample i"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Faster than batch GD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Only computes 1 gradient per step"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hops around path"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Noisy updates cause oscillation toward minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Escapes local minima"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Randomness helps explore optimization landscape"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ideal for large datasets"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Batch GD impossible with billions of samples; SGD works"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mini-batch SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uses B samples (e.g., 32) for balance of speed and stability"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Critical for SGD (constant → overshoot, decay → better convergence)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": η = η₀ / (1 + decay × epoch) at fixed epochs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine annealing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": η follows cosine curve from max to min"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Warmup"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Start small, increase to max, then decrease"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Foundation of deep learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": SGD is the backbone for training neural networks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, SGD is absolutely fundamental: it enables training massive models like GPT-4, DALL-E, and Stable Diffusion by making optimization computationally feasible on billion-sample datasets, escaping local minima in complex non-convex loss surfaces, and adapting to streaming/online learning scenarios; mastering SGD is essential for understanding how modern AI systems learn from data at scale."}]}]}}